15
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15
16
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 37 of Title 72, unless there is
16
17
created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17
18
A. The Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs shall establish
18
19
a program to provide any eligible person or veteran of the Oklahoma
19
20
National Guard who meets the requirements set forth in subsection B
20
21
of this section to receive either a proper memorial headstone or
21
22
marker meeting the same physical standards for size, material,
22
23
composition, placement, and informational content of the provisions
23
24
of 38 U.S.C., Section 2306 or Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00) for
24
Req. No. 2656 Page 1

1
reimbursement for a memorial headstone or marker. The program shall
1
2
provide a burial grant for any veteran or any person who qualifies
2
3
for reimbursement, as determined by the Oklahoma Department of
3
4
Veterans Affairs. Reimbursement shall be provided from the National
4
5
Guard Veteran Burial Revolving Fund established in Section 2 of this
5
6
act.
6
7
B. To be eligible for the program, the member shall:
7
8
1. Have served six (6) or more years in the Oklahoma National
8
9
Guard;
9
10
2. Have died as a resident of this state;
10
11
3. Have been separated or discharged from service honorably or
11
12
under honorable conditions; and
12
13
4. Not qualify to receive a proper memorial headstone or marker
13
14
pursuant to 38 U.S.C., Section 2306.
14
15
C. An application process for the implementation of this
15
16
program shall be developed by the Oklahoma Department of Veterans
16
17
Affairs.
17
18
D. The Oklahoma Veterans Commission shall promulgate any rules
18
19
necessary for the implementation of this act.
19
20
SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20
21
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 38 of Title 72, unless there is
21
22
created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22
23
There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
23
24
to be designated the “National Guard Veteran Burial Revolving Fund”,
24
Req. No. 2656 Page 2

1
which shall be administered by the Oklahoma Department of Veterans
1
2
Affairs. The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal
2
3
year limitations, and shall consist of any legislative
3
4
appropriations, donations, and gifts received from any individuals
4
5
or organizations. All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are
5
6
appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma
6
7
Department of Veterans Affairs to provide a proper memorial
7
8
headstone or marker to an eligible person or veteran of the Oklahoma
8
9
National Guard who meets the requirements set forth in Section 1 of
9
10
this act.
10
11
SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
